---
import ProjectDetailLayout from "../../layouts/ProjectDetailLayout.astro";

const metrics = [
    { label: "Sharpe Ratio", value: "2.1 vs 0.8" },
    { label: "Exec Latency", value: "12ms" },
    { label: "Max Drawdown", value: "-12%" },
    { label: "Alpha", value: "+45%" },
];
---

<ProjectDetailLayout
    title="Multi-Agent RL for High-Frequency Trading"
    description="Orchestrating competitive PPO agents for algorithmic trading in volatile crypto markets with strict risk constraints."
    metrics={metrics}
    github="#"
>
    <h2>Problem & Constraints</h2>
    <p>
        Crypto markets are highly volatile and inefficient, presenting
        opportunities for algorithmic trading. However, traditional strategies
        often fail due to <strong>non-stationary market regimes</strong> and
        <strong>execution slippage</strong>. The goal was to build an RL agent
        capable of adapting to changing volatility while maintaining strict risk
        management (max drawdown less than 15%) and accounting for real-world
        transaction costs.
    </p>

    <h2>Approach</h2>
    <p>
        I treated market making as a multi-agent reinforcement learning (MARL)
        problem:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>
            <strong>Algorithm:</strong>
            <code translate="no">Proximal Policy Optimization (PPO)</code> with a
            custom reward function that penalizes volatility (<code
                translate="no">Sortino Ratio</code
            > optimization).
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Observation Space:</strong> 50ms order book snapshots (L2 data),
            recent trade flow, and technical indicators (<code translate="no"
                >RSI</code
            >, <code translate="no">MACD</code>) normalized via z-score.
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Simulation Environment:</strong> Built a custom high-performance
            backtester using <code translate="no">VectorBT</code> (<code
                translate="no">numba</code
            >-accelerated) to simulate years of L2 data in minutes. Included
            realistic latency (20ms) and fee models (5bps).
        </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Baselines & Evaluation</h2>
    <p>
        Evaluated using <strong>Walk-Forward Analysis</strong> (train on 2018-2020,
        test on Q1 2021, retrain, etc.) to prevent look-ahead bias.
    </p>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse my-6">
            <thead>
                <tr class="border-b border-white/10 text-text-primary">
                    <th class="py-2 px-4">Strategy</th>
                    <th class="py-2 px-4">Annual Return</th>
                    <th class="py-2 px-4">Max Drawdown</th>
                    <th class="py-2 px-4">Sharpe Ratio</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
                    <td class="py-2 px-4">Buy & Hold (BTC)</td>
                    <td class="py-2 px-4">+132%</td>
                    <td class="py-2 px-4">-55%</td>
                    <td class="py-2 px-4">0.85</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
                    <td class="py-2 px-4">Grid Bot (Baseline)</td>
                    <td class="py-2 px-4">+45%</td>
                    <td class="py-2 px-4">-25%</td>
                    <td class="py-2 px-4">1.2</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="bg-accent-primary/5">
                    <td class="py-2 px-4 font-semibold text-accent-primary"
                        ><code translate="no">PPO</code> Agent (Our Method)</td
                    >
                    <td class="py-2 px-4 font-semibold text-accent-primary"
                        >+177%</td
                    >
                    <td class="py-2 px-4 font-semibold text-accent-primary"
                        >-12%</td
                    >
                    <td class="py-2 px-4 font-semibold text-accent-primary"
                        >2.1</td
                    >
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
    </div>

    <h2>Error Analysis & Failure Modes</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>
            <strong>Regime Change Failure:</strong> The model struggled during the
            sudden crash of May 2021.
            <em>Fix:</em> Implemented a "Circuit Breaker" rule—if volatility exceeds
            3-sigma, the agent switches to cash-only mode until stability returns.
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Overfitting to Noise:</strong> Initial models memorized specific
            price patterns.
            <em>Fix:</em> Added domain randomization (randomly scaling price/volume
            inputs by ±5%) during training to force feature learning over pattern
            matching.
        </li>
    </ul>

    <details open>
        <summary>Engineering Notes: Infrastructure Choices</summary>
        <p>
            Switched from standard <code translate="no">Python</code>
            <code translate="no">multiprocessing</code> to <strong
                ><code translate="no">Ray</code></strong
            > for parallel environment rollouts. This scaled training from 4 cores
            to a 64-core <code translate="no">AWS c5.18xlarge</code> spot instance,
            reducing training time from 3 days to 4 hours. Used <code
                translate="no">Redis</code
            > as a high-throughput feature store for live inference.
        </p>
    </details>

    <h2>Productionization</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>
            <strong>Live execution:</strong>
            <code translate="no">Python asyncio</code> service connecting to Exchange
            <code translate="no">Websockets</code>.
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Latency:</strong> End-to-end tick-to-trade latency optimized to
            ~12ms (in same AWS region).
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Monitoring:</strong>
            <code translate="no">Prometheus</code>/<code translate="no"
                >Grafana</code
            > dashboard tracking PnL, open exposure, and API rate limits in real-time.
        </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What I'd Do Next</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>
            Implement <code translate="no">Transformer</code>-based policy
            networks (<code translate="no">Decision Transformer</code>) for
            longer-context reasoning.
        </li>
        <li>Add sentiment analysis features from news APIs.</li>
    </ul>
</ProjectDetailLayout>
